  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide safe water to 200 slum children In India</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">RUCHI (Rural Centre for Human Interests) India plans to distribute 200 water purifiers to 200 children inhabiting in Baddi slums, India.  Safe drinking water is a serious problem in Baddi area.  The slum dwellers are poor migrant people and do not have access to clean water.   To raise family income often their children indulge in rag picking.  Access to safe water will improve child health, check water related diseases  and improve working efficiency of parents.</narrative>
  </description>
